summary_markdown: This table outlines the subdimensions of Brand Building Blocks, structured hierarchically with "Resonance" and "Salience" as overarching categories. Resonance encompasses "Loyalty," "Attachment," "Community," and "Engagement," representing the deepest level of brand connection. Below Resonance, two key dimensions are presented: "Judgments," which includes "Quality," "Credibility," "Consideration," and "Superiority," and "Feelings," comprising "Warmth," "Fun," "Excitement," "Security," "Social Approval," and "Self-Respect." Further down, "Performance" details aspects like "Primary Characteristics and Secondary Features," "Reliability," "Durability," "Serviceability," "Service Effectiveness," "Efficiency," "Empathy," "Style and Design," and "Price." Similarly, "Imagery" covers "User Profiles," "Purchase and Usage Situations," "Personality and Values," and "History, Heritage, and Experiences." Finally, Salience, at the base, is defined by "Category Identification" and "Needs Satisfied," indicating the brand's accessibility and relevance.
